rows.field_524606: Check out this 1.5-mile out-and-back trail near Yellowstone National Park, Wyoming. Generally considered an easy route, it takes an average of 38 min to complete. This is a very popular area for walking, so you'll likely encounter other people while exploring. The best times to visit this trail are April through October. You'll need to leave pups at home ‚Äî dogs aren't allowed on this trail.
rows.field_524777: Went with family. Very nice views and grandma loved it!

rows.field_524606: Experience this 4.5-mile loop trail near Mammoth Cave, Kentucky. Generally considered a moderately challenging route, it takes an average of 1 h 52 min to complete. This is a very popular area for birding, camping, and fishing, so you'll likely encounter other people while exploring. The best times to visit this trail are March through November. Dogs are welcome, but must be on a leash.
rows.field_524777: Did this hike after taking a tour of the cave. It was pretty easy and for the most part flat.

rows.field_524606: Enjoy this 1.8-mile out-and-back trail near Park City, Kentucky. Generally considered an easy route, it takes an average of 46 min to complete. This trail is great for birding and hiking. Dogs are welcome, but must be on a leash.
rows.field_524777: Super easy trail. It's paved and you can take a stroller easily.

rows.field_524606: Experience this 16.0-mile out-and-back trail near Park City, Kentucky. Generally considered a moderately challenging route, it takes an average of 5 h 26 min to complete. Dogs are welcome, but must be on a leash.
